MOTION DOCKET

95-100. Trader v. People Working Cooperatively, Inc. Hamilton County, No. C-930716.

On April 26, 1995, this cause was allowed on a discretionary appeal and held for the decision in 94-405, Haynes v. Zoological Soc. of Cincinnati Hamilton County, Nos. C-910598 and C-910635. The briefing schedule was stayed. See (1995), 72 Ohio St.3d 1415, 647 N.E.2d 1389.

Sua sponte, stay dissolved. The parties are to proceed with briefing on the merits pursuant to the Supreme Court Rules of Practice.
